<p>For advanced users, page-level script and style control is especially powerful.</p>



<p>This feature allows you to disable specific scripts or styles on individual pages. It’s an excellent way to fine-tune performance and have precise control over how each page loads.</p>



<p>As you can see, OceanWP was really fast in my speed tests, loading completely in 3.2 seconds.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="344" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/oceanwp-gtmetrix-a.png" alt="OceanWP's GTmetrix speed test results" class="wp-image-363406" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/oceanwp-gtmetrix-a.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/oceanwp-gtmetrix-a-300x152.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>If you’re building an online store, OceanWP is especially strong. Even in the free version, you’ll get built-in <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/the-ultimate-ecommerce-launch-checklist-for-wordpress/" title="The Ultimate eCommerce Launch Checklist for WordPress">eCommerce</a> features like native cart popups and floating add-to-cart bars, all without needing extra plugins.</p>



<p>Other than that, OceanWP has a library of demo sites you can import with one click. Customizing them is easy thanks to deep integration with the customizer. The theme also works with major page builders like Elementor, <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/beaver-builder/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Beaver Builder Home Page">Beaver Builder</a>, and <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/elegantthemes-divi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="ElegantThemes Divi">Divi</a>.</p>



<p>🧑‍💻 <strong>Why I recommend OceanWP:</strong> If you need a fast theme that can grow with your site, <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/oceanwp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="OceanWP">OceanWP</a> is a top choice. It’s packed with features, works well with WooCommerce, and gives you performance optimization tools you won’t find in most free themes.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-5-generatepress-ultra-lightweight-modular-wordpress-theme"><a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/generatepress/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="GeneratePress">7. GeneratePress – Ultra-Lightweight, Modular WordPress Theme</a></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/generatepress/" target="_blank" rel=" noreferrer noopener nofollow"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="360" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/generatepress.png" alt="GeneratePress" class="wp-image-201709" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/generatepress.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/generatepress-300x159.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></a></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Speed Test Results</strong></td><td>Grade: A, Performance: 89%, TTFB: 839 ms</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pros of GeneratePress</strong></td><td>✅ One of the fastest and lightest themes available<br>✅ Modular design for full control over performance<br>✅ Well-coded, secure, and stable<br>✅ Excellent documentation and active community</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cons of GeneratePress</strong></td><td>❌ Free version is limited in design options<br>❌ Less beginner-friendly if you want pre-styled templates</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pricing</strong></td><td>Free version available or $59/year</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p><a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/generatepress/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="GeneratePress">GeneratePress</a> is one of the fastest themes you can get for WordPress. Its default install is under 10 KB, which makes it incredibly lightweight and quick to load.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-my-experience">My Experience</h5>



<p>What sets GeneratePress apart is its modular design. I like that I could turn features on or off depending on what I needed. This setup enables your site to stay lean and avoid the bloat that often slows down other multipurpose themes.</p>



<p>And since GeneratePress avoids jQuery and uses clean, efficient code, it reduces the risk of <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-check-for-wordpress-plugin-conflicts/" title="How to Check for WordPress Plugin Conflicts">plugin conflicts</a> and helps your site load even faster.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="344" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/generatepress-gtmetrix-a.png" alt="GeneratePress' GTmetrix speed test results" class="wp-image-363390" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/generatepress-gtmetrix-a.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/generatepress-gtmetrix-a-300x152.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>It also works beautifully with the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-use-the-new-wordpress-block-editor/" title="How to Use the WordPress Block Editor (Gutenberg Tutorial)">Gutenberg block editor</a>.</p>



<p>With the premium version, you can build <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-wordpress-full-site-editing-themes/" title="Best Block Themes for Full Site Editing in WordPress">block-based themes</a> and custom layouts without relying on third-party page builders. This keeps your site fast, stable, and easy to manage long-term.</p>



<p>Developers will love the hooks and filters for advanced customization. Meanwhile, beginners will appreciate its stability and reliability.</p>



<p>🧑‍💻 <strong>Why I recommend GeneratePress:</strong> If you want maximum speed and a clean foundation for customization, <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/generatepress/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="GeneratePress">GeneratePress</a> is hard to beat. It’s perfect for performance-focused users who prefer a minimalist, reliable base to build on.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-7-kadencewp-lightweight-wordpress-theme-with-design-controls"><a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/kadence-wp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" title="Kadence WP">8. Kadence WP – Lightweight WordPress Theme with Design Controls</a></h4>



