<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-circle-so-mighty-networks-the-fully-managed-approach">Circle &amp; Mighty Networks: The Fully Managed Approach</h5>



<p>Circle and Mighty Networks take a completely different approach. They handle all security for you behind the scenes as part of their service.</p>



<p>Server hardening, patching software vulnerabilities, monitoring for threats, and managing SSL certificates are all included in your monthly subscription.</p>



<p>Your main responsibility is simply to use a <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-force-strong-password-on-users-in-wordpress/" title="How to Force Strong Passwords on Users in WordPress">strong password</a> for your admin account. This &#8216;done-for-you&#8217; security provides significant peace of mind and is one of the biggest selling points of a hosted platform.</p>



<p>You don&#8217;t have to think about security maintenance. Instead, you can just focus on engaging with your members. The trade-off is that you have no control over the security stack and must trust that their measures are sufficient.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-support-getting-help-when-you-need-it">Support: Getting Help When You Need It</h4>


<div class="wpb-alert style-yellow">

<p>🏅&nbsp;<strong>TL;DR:</strong> BuddyBoss gives you the best of both worlds: dedicated product support combined with the unmatched, free resources and affordable expert help available in the global WordPress community.</p>

</div>


<p>You&#8217;ll eventually have questions no matter which platform you choose. </p>



<p>Let&#8217;s look at how each one provides support when you need help.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-buddyboss-official-support-plus-a-global-community">BuddyBoss: Official Support Plus a Global Community</h5>



<p>BuddyBoss provides support through multiple channels. While they offer standard ticket-based help for technical issues, their real strength lies in the self-service resources they provide.</p>



<p>For immediate answers, their online knowledge base is the first place to look. It&#8217;s detailed and well-organized, covering everything from initial setup to advanced features, making it easy to find solutions on your own.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="380" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/buddyboss-knowledge-base.png" alt="An example of a WordPress knowledge base" class="wp-image-305549" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/buddyboss-knowledge-base.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/buddyboss-knowledge-base-300x168.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Beyond the knowledge base, BuddyBoss invests heavily in user education. They offer a free video course to guide you through getting started, run regular webinars to showcase new features, and maintain an active blog with tips and best practices.</p>



<p>Finally, because BuddyBoss is built on WordPress, you also have the support of the entire global community. This means access to thousands of free tutorials and the ability to easily&nbsp;<a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-places-to-hire-wordpress-developers/" title="Best Places to Hire WordPress Developers (Expert Pick)">find an affordable WordPress developer</a>&nbsp;if you ever need custom help.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-circle-so-mighty-networks-dedicated-support-and-peer-communities">Circle &amp; Mighty Networks: Dedicated Support and Peer Communities</h5>



<p>Circle and Mighty Networks provide a direct line of support from their own expert teams. When you submit a ticket, you are talking to the people who build and maintain the platform every day. This is excellent for any questions related to their platform&#8217;s specific features.</p>



<p>Both platforms also have extensive, searchable knowledge bases with step-by-step guides and video tutorials. They also provide support through their own customer-only communities.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="393" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/mightynetworks-support-community.png" alt="Mighty Networks Support Community" class="wp-image-362614" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/mightynetworks-support-community.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/mightynetworks-support-community-300x173.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>By joining, you get peer-to-peer help from other successful community builders, allowing you to ask for advice and share best practices with people who are using the exact same tools as you.</p>



<p>The main limitation is that this support ecosystem is closed. If you have a problem that goes beyond a standard feature, like trying to add a piece of custom code, you&#8217;re on your own.</p>



<p>The pool of outside experts for these closed platforms is very small compared to the vast WordPress community.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-monetization-and-true-cost">Monetization and True Cost: Which Platform Is More Profitable?</h4>


<div class="wpb-alert style-yellow">

<p>🏅 <strong>TL;DR: </strong>While the upfront cost for the license and hosting might seem higher than a basic SaaS plan, BuddyBoss is the clear winner for long-term value.</p>



<p>By eliminating platform transaction fees, you keep 100% of your revenue, which can save you thousands of dollars every year as your community grows. You are investing in an asset you own, not paying a percentage of your success to a rented platform.</p>

</div>


<p>It is important to look beyond the initial monthly fee to understand the true cost of each platform. This includes annual licenses, hosting costs, and transaction fees, which can become a major expense.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-the-buddyboss-model-annual-license-hosting">The BuddyBoss Model: Annual License + Hosting</h5>



<p>BuddyBoss operates on the standard premium WordPress plugin model. When you break it down, the costs are straightforward and give you full control.</p>



<p>Here&#8217;s an overview: </p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Annual License Fee:</strong> This starts at $299/year and covers the software, support, and all future updates.</li>



<li><strong>WordPress Hosting:</strong> You choose and pay for your own <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-hosting/" title="How to Choose the Best WordPress Hosting">hosting</a>. This is a huge advantage, as you can start small with an affordable provider and upgrade only when you need to.</li>



<li><strong>Transaction Fees:</strong> BuddyBoss charges 0% in platform fees. When you sell memberships with a plugin like <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/solutions/memberpress" title="MemberPress Review">MemberPress</a>, you only pay standard fees to your payment processor (like Stripe or PayPal). Every dollar after that is yours.</li>
</ul>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-the-saas-model-all-in-one-subscription-transaction-fees">The SaaS Model: All-in-One Subscription + Transaction Fees</h5>



<p>Circle and Mighty Networks offer an appealing all-in-one monthly subscription. While simple, it&#8217;s important to be aware of the transaction fees that are built into this model.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Monthly Subscription:</strong> Starts at $49/month and includes the software, hosting, and security. This offers predictable, fixed costs.</li>



<li><strong>Platform Transaction Fees:</strong> This is the key additional cost. On their entry-level plans, Circle takes a 4% fee and Mighty Networks takes a 3% fee from all the revenue you generate.</li>



<li><strong>Processor Fees:</strong> The platform fees mentioned above are in addition to the standard processing fees charged by Stripe.</li>
</ul>



<p>That extra percentage might not seem like much at first, but it quickly becomes a huge expense.</p>



<p>If your community generates $50,000 in revenue in a year, you would be paying an extra $2,000 to Circle or $1,500 to Mighty Networks, just in platform fees. With the BuddyBoss and MemberPress combination, that money would have stayed in your pocket.</p>



